## üîç Quick Search Commands

*Use these commands to find relevant documentation*

### Search for Keyword

```bash
# Search all docs for keyword
grep -r "keyword" docs/ --include="*.md"

# Case-insensitive search
grep -ri "keyword" docs/ --include="*.md"

# Search with context (3 lines before/after)
grep -ri -C 3 "keyword" docs/ --include="*.md"
```

### List All Documents

```bash
# All markdown files
find docs/ -name "*.md" -type f | sort

# Recently modified (last 7 days)
find docs/ -name "*.md" -type f -mtime -7

# Large documents (>50 KB)
find docs/ -name "*.md" -type f -size +50k
```

### Search by Directory

```bash
# Active work
ls -lah docs/active/

# Completed phases
ls -lah docs/phases/completed/

# Architecture docs
ls -lah docs/architecture/
```

### Using Artisan Command

```bash
# Quick search with artisan
php artisan docs:search "keyword"

# Generate fresh docs index
php artisan knowledge:generate-docs-index
```
